{"word":"H1238 - בָּקַק - bâqaq - baw-kah' - Empty","slug":"H1238","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">בָּקַק</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>bâqaq"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>baw-kah'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Empty"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D1;&#x05BC;&#x05E7;&#x05E7; - ba&#x0302;qaq</b> - <i>baw-kah'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>pour</i> out, that is, to <i>empty</i>, figuratively to <i>depopulate</i>; by analogy to <i>spread</i> out (as a fruitful vine): - (make) empty (out), fail, X utterly, make void."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1227\">H1227</a>, <a href=\"#/H1228\">H1228</a>, <a href=\"#/H1229\">H1229</a>, <a href=\"#/H2999\">H2999</a>"}]}